<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150525>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. A–Tomopterna tuberculosa (Boulenger, 1882), illustration of the type by Ģnther (1865); C–A typical T. tuberculosa morph (PEM A15131) from Ongongo, Namibia (Photo A. Channing).; E–A brown T. tuberculosa morph (PEM A15137) from Dumbo, Angola (Photo A. Channing). B–preserved Tomopterna pulchra (Boulenger, 1896) (PEM A15100) from Muso Hills, Zambia (Photo A. Channing); D–PEM A15100 in life (Photo F. Willems); F–Specimen (PEM A15134) from Iringa, Tanzania (Photo A. Channing)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150525/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150535>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Distribution of genetically confirmed records of T. tuberculosa (blue circles) and T. pulchra (red squares). Type localities indicated by stars. Arid corridor indicated by a dashed line." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150535/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

